'''Zaff''' is a salesman who owns [[Zaff's Superior Staves]] in the city of [[Varrock]]. He is located in his shop just north-west of [[Varrock]] centre. His shop is often visited because it is one of the few places that sells [[battlestaff|battlestaves]], the other being [[Baba Yaga]] on [[Lunar Isle]]. He is also involved in the [[What Lies Below]] quest. During the quest, players can summon him by using a [[beacon ring]] and [[Zaff's instructions]].

Zaff is secretly a member of the [[Varrock Palace Secret Guard]] (likely accounting for his shop's proximity to it), known to [[Rat Burgiss]], and it appears his proficiency at magic is far higher than many would presume, as it was he who possessed the Beacon and used a spell to counter [[Surok Magis|Surok]]'s mind control spell, disabling Surok's teleportation magic and imprisoning him in the library.

==Battlestaves==
Zaff sells noted [[battlestaff|battlestaves]] for {{NoCoins|7,000}} [[coins]] each, in the barrel found in the corner of his shop. Depending on the tier of [[Varrock Diary]] completed, players will be able to buy battlestaves from his barrel daily. A player must claim their diary reward from [[Toby]] before collecting their tier of battlestaves from Zaff. The battlestaves restock daily at 00:00 UTC.

*'''Easy''': 15 battlestaves for a total of 105,000 gp for a profit of {{Coins|{{GEP|Battlestaff|15}}-105000}}
*'''Medium''': 30 battlestaves for a total of 210,000 gp for a profit of {{Coins|{{GEP|Battlestaff|30}}-210000}}
*'''Hard''': 60 battlestaves for a total of 420,000 gp for a profit of {{Coins|{{GEP|Battlestaff|60}}-420000}}
*'''Elite''': 120 battlestaves for a total of 840,000 gp for a profit of {{Coins|{{GEP|Battlestaff|120}}-840000}}

The battlestaves are claimed to be discounted, however they cost the same as the normal store price. The only possible "discount" is that their price does not increase as stock decreases, saving the player at most a few thousand gold per day.

Completing a harder diary after claiming battlestaves for the day will NOT reset the stock. For example: completing the Easy diary and claiming 15 battlestaves, then completing the Medium diary and attempting to claim battlestaves again will tell you to come back tomorrow. Therefore it is recommended to claim your battlestaves after completing any diaries you plan to do today.

